detaileddescription.para: Reference to the original tree this root proxies. When the RootProxy is adopted by a command, this is used as key to route 'reply' messages.
This is the link to the original 'remote'. It is used to send queries to the remote tree.
The link to the proxy factory is used by the RootProxy when it needs to create new ObjectProxies.
Class signature. Create a proxy from a remote end_point. Do not build meta methods.
This method is used to send a message to the remote tree.
Keep proxy in sync by parsing replies and sending new queries.
Set proxy's factory (used to create new object proxies). this method registers the RootProxy into the given factory.
Returns the location of the original tree this proxy mirrors.
Dynamically build a child from the given name. If type is empty, we build dummy object proxies that will try to get a "type" from the remote end.
IF the RootProxy was adopted by a Command, this removes the link making it an orphan.
Set proxy's command (communication channel). this method registers the RootProxy into the given command.
Called by ~Command to avoid further 'unregister' calls.

Get information on the direct children of the remote root: this method should not be used (automatically called during startup). The argument is just here to give the same signature as ObjectProxy::sync_children.
This class helps maintain a 'ghost' tree that mirrors a remote 'real' tree. It is usually used as an element from an interface to interact with some remote device.
